    "This significant technological innovation is liable to exacerbate ethical challenges already present in traditional public opinion research.",
    "AI polling has, for the most part, been applied to the issue of pre-election polling.",
    "While 3 The term is loosely defined in the literature.",
    "The classic definition by Laney et al. (2001) relies on the '3Vs': Volume-the size of the data in terms of the number of observations and measurable dimensions; Velocity-the frequency over time at which new observations are generated; Variety-the degree to which the underlying data is structured (e.g., a classic survey) or unstructured (e.g., the output from a social-media API).",
    "4 This evidence comes from recent high-profile polling failures, namely, the the 2015 election in the UK which saw the conservative vote under-estimated by around 4% at the national level, and the US 2016 election which saw correct national estimation of preferences but substantial sub-national under-estimation of Trump support."
